The paper discusses the phenomenon of over-parametrization in deep networks and its relation to generalization error, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and specifically in the sub-category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of trigonometric polynomials in function approximation, which is a topic in the sub-category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of maximum loss functional and gives estimates on generalization error, which are topics in the sub-category of "Information Theory" (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the construction of neural and RBF networks, which are topics in the sub-category of "Signal and Image Processing" (cs.SI) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI).
